The paper deals with the problem of dictionary learning for tensor data, which involves linear combinations of structured dictionary atoms observed through noise. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the sample complexity of dictionary learning, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper includes numerical experiments on image data, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
